President Donald J. Trump held meetings with Italian President Sergio Mattarella and Prime Minister Paolo Gentiloni. They discussed the alliance between the United States and Italy, with a focus on defense cooperation, counterterrorism, and efforts to deny terrorists safe havens. President Trump thanked Italy for its contributions to global counterterrorism efforts and its participation in the Global Coalition to Counter ISIS. He also praised Italy's diplomatic efforts to end violence in Libya. The leaders reaffirmed transatlantic unity in holding Russia accountable for its actions in Crimea and eastern Ukraine. They also discussed goals for the upcoming G7 Summit.